Lenovo Says Quake-Related Supply Disruptions Eased, WSJ Reports

-- B y   J o s h u a   F e l l m a n
-- 
2011-04-07T22:00:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-07/lenovo-says-quake-related-supply-disruptions-eased-wsj-reports.html
Lenovo Group Ltd. (992) ’s concerns about
disruptions to its parts-supply system caused by  Japan ’s
earthquake last month have eased, the Wall Street Journal said,
citing Chief Operating Officer Rory Read.  The computer maker has closed gaps in supplies that were
mainly related to "second- and third-tier" parts, Read said, as
cited by the newspaper.   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Fellman at 
